    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-05-16T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-05-16T17:00:00-05:00" n="98"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d98">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.51W89 U.S.S.R./55: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_BWC1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bullitt</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-05-16T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 16, 1934—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>80. Your 84, May 16, 1 p.m. Your question No. 4 is not clear to the Department.
                    It may be said that it is contemplated that the Bank will assist in financing a
                    sufficient volume of transactions in the 20-year period to produce out of
                    additional interest amount of money necessary to repay agreed indebtedness and
                    interest thereon. The aggregate amount of the credits which will be facilitated
                    or approved by the Bank during that period will probably exceed double the
                    amount of the agreed indebtedness. See paragraph 4 in Department’s 72, May 11, 6
                    p.m. Bank can not specify in advance what percentage of credit in any given
                    transaction exporter will not be expected to carry.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HC1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
